  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in serious criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Potential prison sentences:\n- Up to 20 years per money laundering offense\n- Maximum sentences can increase for more complex cases\n- Potential additional years if tied to other criminal activities\n\n2. Financial penalties:\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Often up to $500,000 or twice the value of property involved\n- Potential forfeiture of assets connected to laundering\n\n3. Additional consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential loss of professional licenses\n- Immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nSpecific penalties depend on case details, amount of money involved, prior criminal history, and specific circumstances of the offense.\n\nNote: This is general legal information. For specific legal advice about a particular situation, consulting a qualified attorney is recommended.",
